SIMPLE: requite
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Requite
<hw>Re"quite"</hw> <pr>(r?-kw?t")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Requited</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Requiting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>re-</ets> + <ets>quit</ets>.]</ety> <def>To repay; in a good sense,
to recompense; to return (an equivalent) in good; to reward; in a bad
sense, to retaliate; to return (evil) for evil; to punish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He can <qex>requite</qex> thee; for he knows the charma⟦br⟧
That call fame on such gentle acts as these.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou hast seen it; for thou beholdest mischief and spite, to
<qex>requite</qex> it with thy hand.</q> <rj><qau>Ps. x.
14.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To repay; reward; pay; compensate; remunerate;
satisfy; recompense; punish; revenge.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Requitement</ent>⟦br⟧
